    {
      "id": "4d3bf12e-3f0b-4750-9b13-cd419f89d08d",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "To address this limitation, the authors propose a combination of LLMs and Graph Neural Networks that receive,as inputs, data from multiple types of sources. The model uses a bipartite graph to represent student answers. Then, they apply constrastive learning to the signed graphs and combine them with knowledge point embeddings created by the LLM.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "4d3bf12e-3f0b-4750-9b13-cd419f89d08d",
        "parent": {
